Wash and dry all produce.

Quarter @lime{1}. Trim and slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of @chipotle powder{pinch} until smooth. Add @coleslaw mix{4%ounce} and scallion greens; toss to coat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use ½ tsp sugar instead.

> TIP: Taste the slaw and add another pinch or two of chipotle powder if you like things spicy.

Pat @Standard Meat Cast-Iron Seared Chicken Breasts{9%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; thinly slice crosswise.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken, scallion whites, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is warmed through and scallion whites are softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with chicken mixture and slaw. Sprinkle with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} and serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.